The paper deals with the problem of distributed lossy linear function computation in a tree network, which involves information theory and networked systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the quantification of information loss and the rate distortion function, which are related to statistical inference and machine learning, respectively. Hence, cs.SI (Statistical Learning) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of network computation rate and rate allocation, which are related to distributed computing and algorithms. Therefore, cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is another possible sub-category.
